The paper deals with image-based garment transfer, which involves tasks related to computer vision (CV) such as pose estimation, segmentation, and image generation. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with graphics (GR) as it involves generating new images of the wearer dressed in arbitrary garments. The use of generative adversarial methods also falls under the sub-category of multimedia (MM). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as generative adversarial networks (GANs), which fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI).
